Interface DataImporter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InitialDataAppointments, InitialDataAppointmentSlots, InitialDataMedicalRecord, InitialDataMedicine, InitialDataPatient, InitialDatareplenishmentRequest, InitialDataStaff

    public interface DataImporter
    The DataImporter interface defines the contract for importing and reloading data from files. Classes implementing this interface must provide implementations for importing data from a file, reloading data, and handling data import logic.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void importData()
      Handles the data import process, which may involve loading data from multiple sources or performing specific initialization tasks.
      void importDatafromFile(java.lang.String filename)
      Imports data from the specified file.

      Reloads data from the default data source or file.
